<subSubSection pageId="11" pageNumber="50" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="11.[151,1436,151,824]" pageId="11" pageNumber="50">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[197,332,764,788]" pageId="11" pageNumber="50">Etymology.</emphasis>
The specific name is derived from the combined Latin word “ 
<taxonomicName box="[1071,1194,764,788]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Aguriahana" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="50" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="recticornis">recticornis</taxonomicName>
” which refers to the straight processes of the aedeagal shaft.
</paragraph>
